President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. These include Bruce H. Andrews as Deputy Secretary of the Department of Commerce, Marcia Stephens Bloom Bernicat as Ambassador to the People's Republic of Bangladesh, Marcus D. Jadotte as Assistant Secretary for Industry and Analysis at the Department of Commerce, James D. Pettit as Ambassador to the Republic of Moldova, and Laura S. Wertheimer as Inspector General of the Federal Housing Finance Agency. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Caitlin K. Cahow as a member of the President's Council on Fitness, Sports, and Nutrition, Steven Croley as a member of the Council of the Administrative Conference of the United States, Jane Jelenko as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council, Brig. Gen. John S. Kem as Commissioner of the Mississippi River Commission, George A. Elmaraghy as Commissioner of the Ohio River Valley Water Sanitation Commission, Tom FitzGerald as Commissioner of the Ohio River Valley Water Sanitation Commission, and Susan Hedman as Commissioner of the Ohio River Valley Water Sanitation Commission. President Obama stated that he is honored to have these individuals join his administration and looks forward to working with them in the future.